      • setTextBegin

        public void setTextBegin(int textNr,
                         int textBegin)
        Sets the beginning index for the text with number textNr to the index textBegin. Ensures that all text begins are set sequentially and checks that the begin index is preceded by a '$' in the actual input read so far.
        Parameters:
        textNr - The nr of the text to set.
        textBegin - The index of the text's first character in the total input.
